description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Successful candidates will be invited to an Assessment Day on Friday 18th December. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this will be either a morning or afternoon session to be confirmed&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking mental health or learning disabilities nurses who are passionate about providing high quality patient care, working in a dynamic and forward thinking environment on our acute assessment units based in Bodmin. Fletcher Ward provides care, treatment and support to any person experiencing mental illness and need admission.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are committed to developing our staff and provide a full Corporate Curriculum training programme which will support your learning and development into the future.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants should be willing to work long days on a rotational shift pattern, 7 days/nights a fortnight including weekends. Part time rotational hours may be considered. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Whether you’re already living in Cornwall or looking to gain valuable adult mental health acute experience you could take the next step in your career and benefit from living in a beautiful part of the country whilst making a real difference to patients. We are proud of our innovative and patient safety focused culture.&lt;br /&gt;There is a strong positive multi-disciplinary team on the unit and we are happy to consider those who do not have recent adult acute experience.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Interview expenses and relocation fees of up to £3k will be considered for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full and part time hours available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Christie, Ward Manager 01208 251377&lt;/p&gt;
